{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|木|人|c1=s|t1=tree|c2=s|t2=a person|ls=ic}}. On bronze inscription, a foot [[夂]] was added at the bottom of the character. Later, the two components on top were highly compressed and stylized into [[圥]] (with a variant [[𡴆]]). Its original meaning was perhaps "to climb; to surpass".

